list.title: Collision.isCollide
list.description: A static method that checks whether two particles are colliding

list.title: Constraint#particles
list.description: Calculates the list of particles that is involved with the constraint

list.title: Constraint#vertices
list.description: Calculates the list of vertices that will be used in the rendering process

list.title: HashGridItem#getHashDimensions
list.description: Computes the dimensions of the item for the HashGrid.

list.title: HashGridItem#getHashPos
list.description: Computes the coordinate position for the item within the HashGrid, expects center position.

list.title: InputHandler#addKeyEvent
list.description: Adds a KeyInput to the list of events that the InputHandler tracks

list.title: InputHandler#startKeyHandling
list.description: Begins key tracking (must be called for key interactions)

list.title: InputHandler#startMouseHandling
list.description: Begins mouse tracking (must be called for mouse interactions)

list.title: NearBehavior#range
list.description: Returns the effective range / defines the size of the nearby range

list.title: PenaltyCollision.isCollide
list.description: A static method that checks whether two particles are colliding

list.title: PowderForce#findDensity
list.description: Calculates the approximate density within the effective radius of the particle

list.title: Pressure#findDensity
list.description: Calculates the approximate density within the effective radius of the particle

list.title: RectangularWorldBoundary#isCollide
list.description: Checks if a Particle is colliding with the Wall

list.title: Renderer#renderFrame
list.description: Renders a single frame of the solver

list.title: Renderer#updateContext
list.description: Updates the HTMLCanvas context of each sub-renderer

list.title: Renderer#updateRendererParticles
list.description: Updates the particles in the particleRenderer. Must be called every time the list of particles is reassigned.

list.title: Solver#solve
list.description: Solves one iteration of the current physics world

list.title: Solver#update
list.description: Optional function that can be defined to exhibit certain behavior in the solve loop.

list.title: Solver#updateSolverParticles
list.description: Update the particle positions in the SpatialHashGrid

list.title: SpatialHashGrid#findNear
list.description: Finds the nearby items for a given item, and updates the queryId.

list.title: SpatialHashGrid#updateItem
list.description: Updates the grid positions of the item within the HashGrid. This function MUST be called after any position change.

list.title: SpatialHashGrid#values
list.description: Returns a unique list of all HashGridItems the HashGrid.

list.title: Vector2D#add
list.description: returns a new added vector denoted by this + v.

list.title: Vector2D#addTo
list.description: adds a vector to the current vector (this = this + v).

list.title: Vector2D#cross
list.description: returns the "cross-product" of two vectors (this and v). Since these are 2D vectors, this is the z-coordinate of the 3D counter parts of these 2D vectors. It returns a scalar.

list.title: Vector2D#dot
list.description: returns the dot product of two vectors (this and v).

list.title: Vector2D#magSqr
list.description: returns the magnitude squared of the vector.

list.title: Vector2D#mult
list.description: returns a new scalar-multiplied vector denoted by this * a.

list.title: Vector2D#multTo
list.description: multiplies a scalar to the current vector (this = this * a).

list.title: Vector2D#reflect
list.description: Performs the mirror reflection for this about a normal vector.

list.title: Vector2D#reflectTo
list.description: Performs the mirror reflection for this about a normal vector. (modifies self)

list.title: Vector2D#sub
list.description: returns a new subtracted vector denoted by this - v.

list.title: Vector2D#subTo
list.description: subtracts a vector to the current vector (this = this - v).

list.title: Wall#applyCorrection
list.description: Applies positional corrections on particles (walls do not move)

list.title: Wall#resolveCollisions
list.description: Resolve the collisions between the surrounding particles and the Wall itself.

list.title: WallBoundary#isCollide
list.description: Checks if a Particle is colliding with the Wall

list.title: World#addGlobalNearBehavior
list.description: Adds a NearBehavior to all the particles in the world

list.title: World#addGlobalSelfBehavior
list.description: Adds a SelfBehavior to all the particles in the world

list.title: World#clearParticles
list.description: Clears all of the particles and any associated constraints

list.title: World#constrainBoundary
list.description: Creates a RectangularWorldBoundary that confines the boundary of the world with rigid collisions. Also sets this.worldConstraint.

list.title: World#disableChargeInteractions
list.description: Removes the global ChargeInteraction behavior and sets this.chargeBehavior to null

list.title: World#disableCollisions
list.description: Removes the global gravity behavior and sets this.collision to null

list.title: World#disableDrag
list.description: Removes existing drag behavior and sets this.drag to null

list.title: World#disableGravity
list.description: Removes the global gravity behavior and sets this.gravity to null

list.title: World#enableChargeInteractions
list.description: Removes existing ChargeInteraction behavior and adds a new global ChargeInteraction behavior to all the particles, while updating this.chargeBehavior

list.title: World#enableCollisions
list.description: Removes existing collision behavior and adds a new global collision behavior to all the particles, while updating this.collision

list.title: World#enableDrag
list.description: Removes existing drag behavior and adds a new global drag behavior with a given viscosity to all the particles, while updating this.drag

list.title: World#enableGravity
list.description: Removes existing gravity and adds a new global gravity behavior to all the particles, while updating this.gravity

list.title: World#freePivot
list.description: Frees a particle from being a "mass-pivot". This attempts to correct the mass increase from the makePivot() method. Once again, it may not work properly :skull:.

list.title: World#makePivot
list.description: Make a particle a "mass-pivot" by adding a PositionLock behavior and setting the adds Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER / 10 to the particle mass. This is a work around and may cause some other physics to break. This particle pivot will not work with position constraints.

list.title: World#removeGlobalNearBehavior
list.description: Removes a NearBehavior to all the particles in the world

list.title: World#removeGlobalSelfBehavior
list.description: Removes a SelfBehavior from all the particles in the world

list.title: World#setSolverUpdate
list.description: Sets the optional update() function for the solver.

list.title: World#updateParticleList
list.description: Update the list of particles. Must be called every time the number of particles change.
